<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="proud-adj">proud <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /praʊd/    美 /praʊd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>骄傲的；自豪的</strong></h4>
<p>反 ashamed ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a proud look
得意的表情</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) proud of sb / sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We are very proud of ourselves and believe we can do more for a better world.
我们非常自豪，并相信为了让世界更美好，我们可以做得更多。</p><footer>2016 北京书面表达</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) proud to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is proud to have taken part in competitions and to have broken a record.
她对自己参加比赛并打破了纪录感到自豪。</p><footer>人教⑦ – 1</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) proud + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was proud that her daughter had so much talent.
女儿这么有天赋，她很自豪。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[含贬义] 妄自尊大的；自负的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is too proud to see her own mistake.
她太自负了，看不到自己的错误。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>proudly /'praʊdli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Hans Zhang was <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (自豪的) of himself for not giving up.   （2015 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. proud  </p></div>